OL,3,C'They've been forgotten': Parents at
OL,4,CRAAC school worry for children's exams
OL,6,FParents are becoming increasingly
OL,7,Fconcerned about the impact on pupils,
OL,8,Fwho are soon to to sit their GCSE and
OL,9,FA-Level exams.
OL,11,FOne parent told ITV Tyne Tees: "We
OL,12,Fneed equity because we need equality
OL,13,Ffor the children that have been
OL,14,Fimpacted. It feels like these children
OL,15,Fhave been forgotten.
OL,17,F"This is their future. This is their
OL,18,Funiversity places, their college
OL,19,Fplaces, their apprenticeships."
